🚪🤖 Automatic Door Opener with Face Detection

📌 Problem Statement:
Traditional door locks are prone to security risks and require physical interaction.
Keys can be lost, codes forgotten, and unauthorized access remains a constant threat. 🔐❌

🎯 Objective:
Build a smart access system that uses facial recognition powered by OpenCV
to automatically unlock doors — no keys, no codes, just your face! 😎✨

🛠️ Hardware & Software Requirements:
• 🖥️ Raspberry Pi (or laptop for testing)
• 📷 USB Camera
• 🐍 OpenCV (Python) for real-time face detection & recognition
• ⚙️ Servo Motor (to control the door lock mechanism)
• 🔌 Jumper wires, battery pack

🔬 How It Works:
1️⃣ The camera captures live video feed
2️⃣ OpenCV processes each frame to detect and recognize faces
3️⃣ If an authorized face is detected ✅, the servo motor unlocks the door
4️⃣ If unrecognized ❌, access is denied and an alert can be triggered

🏆 Expected Outcome:
A face-based automatic door opener — enhancing security 🔒 and offering
a completely hands-free, contactless access solution. Perfect for smart homes,
offices, and restricted areas! 🏠🏢

💡 Technologies Used: Python | OpenCV | Raspberry Pi | Servo Motor | IoT

